				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$(w,w')$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M94"><mml:mrow><mml:mo stretchy="false">(</mml:mo><mml:mi>w</mml:mi><mml:mo>,</mml:mo><mml:msup><mml:mi>w</mml:mi><mml:mo>′</mml:mo></mml:msup><mml:mo stretchy="false">)</mml:mo></mml:mrow></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="13015_2020_164_Article_IEq47.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula>, where <italic>w</italic> is the accumulated weight of the key, and <inline-formula id="IEq48"><alternatives><tex-math id="M95">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$w'$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M96"><mml:msup><mml:mi>w</mml:mi><mml:mo>′</mml:mo></mml:msup></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="13015_2020_164_Article_IEq48.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula> the accumulated weight of its inverse. When the trie is accessed for a key the first time, the value is initialized with (0, 0). For further observations of the same split, the corresponding entry is increased. Figure <xref rid="Fig1" ref-type="fig">1</xref> shows an example.<fig id="Fig1"><label>Fig. 1</label><caption><p>Toy example for accumulating weights in a trie. The set of genomes <inline-formula id="IEq92"><alternatives><tex-math id="M97">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
