    <p id="Par35">The overall method SANS is shown in Algorithm 1, the very last step of which will be motivated in the following. <graphic position="anchor" xlink:href="13015_2020_164_Figa_HTML" id="MO1"/></p>
    <p id="Par36"><italic>Combining splits and their inverses</italic>. To combine an ordered split (<italic>A</italic>, <italic>B</italic>) of weight <inline-formula id="IEq49"><alternatives><tex-math id="M109">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$w_A$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M110"><mml:msub><mml:mi>w</mml:mi><mml:mi>A</mml:mi></mml:msub></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="13015_2020_164_Article_IEq49.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula> and its inverse (<italic>B</italic>, <italic>A</italic>) of weight <inline-formula id="IEq50"><alternatives><tex-math id="M111">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$w_B$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M112"><mml:msub><mml:mi>w</mml:mi><mml:mi>B</mml:mi></mml:msub></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="13015_2020_164_Article_IEq50.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula>, a naive argument would be: both indicate the same separation, so they should be taken into account equivalently, and thus take the sum <inline-formula id="IEq51"><alternatives><tex-math id="M113">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$w_A + w_B$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M114"><mml:mrow><mml:msub><mml:mi>w</mml:mi><mml:mi>A</mml:mi></mml:msub><mml:mo>+</mml:mo><mml:msub><mml:mi>w</mml:mi><mml:mi>B</mml:mi></mml:msub></mml:mrow></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="13015_2020_164_Article_IEq51.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula> or arithmetic mean <inline-formula id="IEq52"><alternatives><tex-math id="M115">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
