    <p id="Par42">Each genome contributes to at most <italic>O</italic>(<italic>m</italic>) ordered splits. So the sum of the cardinality of all ordered splits, i.e., the total length of all splits in Algorithm 1, is <inline-formula id="IEq72"><alternatives><tex-math id="M237">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
